cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about improving pre-trained language models for natural language understanding tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method on multiple NLU tasks, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another possible category. The paper also mentions the use of RoBERTa as the backbone encoder, which is a neural network architecture, indicating cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another potential category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing techniques, which could suggest cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as a less likely but still possible category.
